Tags:	    Light drop-down terminal
Comments:       Unfortunately this software don't work with ash
				(the default tinycore shell), but work correctly
				with bash, I recommend to install it, edit
				 ~/.Xdefaults and add the program in
				 ~/.xsession to autostart.
				
				This is an example of a string add to ~/.Xdefaults:
				stjerm.key: backslash
				stjerm.mod: alt
				stjerm.shell: /bin/bash
				stjerm.autohide: false
				stjerm.font: 16
				stjerm.foreground: gray
				stjerm.width: 100%
				stjerm.height: 60%
				stjerm.scrollbar: right
				stjerm.allowreorder
                
                The package stjerm-doc.tcz contains man pages with
                all option of the program
